  "StockRole": "Sniper",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Katana began its existence when the Draconis Combine was given several downgraded Crockett BattleMechs by ComStar as part of Operation Rosebud. Independence Weaponry reverse-engineered the weapons so they could produce copies at a nearby facility and closely examined the Crocketts for several months. After making minor modifications these 'Mechs were renamed Katanas and used to replace Chargers in several DCMS units. The Katana quickly become a mainstay in many of the heavier mobile line units, especially after the invention of the C3 Computer. The Katana still shares many of the same features as the Crockett, right down to the serial number.",
